Cell Blockage: Volume 52

Anniversaire

 

Today marks the beginning of a new year, work year, that is.  Today is my "Official" One Year Anniversary at Fremont.  While, as you may know, it has ACTUALLY been more like THREE years, but I was temp for two of those years.  I really can't stand (err... believe) that I've been here this long.  I am no less a lifer than Dina now... someone HELP ME!  I was looking online for a new job last night, but I got distracted.  I guess I'm gonna look into getting some cheap internet sometime in the near future.  I'm kinda over using my phone, but only cuz there are certain things a phone can't do that a pc CAN... like send msgs on myspace, or nav. more than one page at once, ya know?  I kinda miss it.  I try to be TechNO, but I'm tech-y(es), there's no denying it. 

 

Alright, with all that said, I move on to the fact that my birthday KEEEEEEEPSS COMING! hahahaha Today I got to work and Gloria gave me my birthday gift.  You know how she is... she just forgot it had been my birthday, HAHAHA.  Anyway, I like my long long birthday, let's keep it going ALL YEAR!  I wanna celebrate my birthday at Oktoberfest... that is my newest goal.

 

Speaking of goals... I have set quite a few of them, but reasonable ones.  My worst habit is not that I set too many goals but I tend to set the goals higher than I can accomplish in a short per. of time, and if you know me, you know I'm not the most patient girl, so I just end up half-meeting my goals and then losing interest.  SO as part of my resolution, I have decided to not expect too much of myself, and instead, allow myself to relax a little while slowly taking care of my main goals.  This is working thus far, but then again, we're only 2 weeks into the year, hahaha. 

 

How was everyone's weekend?  Mine was amusing at best, I think.  Friday was Karaoke at Volk's house, where Nick and I just sang and sang and drank and sang and drank and drank and sang, whilst Volk and Kyle just laughed and laughed at us all the while... it was fun.  I wouldn't say it was the best thing I've done all year, but it was still fun.  :)  Saturday, Volk and I went to get a gift and to Flamebroiler for some bowls, then to a BABY SHOWER.  YES, a unisex baby shower.  Now let me make it clear that I don't like baby showers, but this one went from TWO until SIX!!!!! Longest baby shower I have ever and WILL ever go to.  I can't say it wasn't full of laughs though... cuz it was, but still... never again.  hahaha 

 

Sunday morning I awoke to Volk playing with my hair or rubbing my arm or something (can't QUITE remember cuz I was so tired still)... he had gotten up and gotten ready to go and told me to get ready, too.  I had to take him to the airport... so now he's in Vegas having the time of his life, I'm sure, and we all have to work.  BOOOOOO....

 

I told him that in April we are going somewhere, on vacation... for a WEEK!  That will give me time enough to gather up some moolah and whatnot.  I dunno where, but I wanna go SOMEWHERE. 

 

Does anyone have any (realistic) ideas? 

 

Alright... for now, this concludes Volume 52 of Cell Blockage... it's a classic. :)
NOTE: Cell Blockage: Volume 51 has been lost.  If you have it, send it to me via email (work or home).

Cell Blockage: Volume 50
The Final Frontier
 
    Hello and welcome back to Cell Blockage.    This is Volume 50, the great and powerful!    Since the last CB, there have been alot of momentus events I won't mention.    I am a what is now and what is to come girl, not a what has been girl.    Respect.    Not that any of you know what that is.
 
    Today is Thursday, December 7th, 2006, and the reason I chose to FINALLY put out Volume 50 is because I can now send it to Deb, too!    That's not completely the reason, but it's all I'm going to say.    I'm really just "feelin" the Cell Blockage today, which I have NOT in some time...  how long has it been?    Anyway, that's how long it's been since I felt like it.    Actually, to be precise, the last CB (Volume 49.5) was put out on Thursday, November 9th, 2006.    That was a long time ago...
 
    Ok... on to happenings.    Popozao is now Nonozao.    Britney's gonch is alllll over the net, fully exposed, on "accident".    I'm sorry but nobody "forgets" to wear panties, and nobody doesn't notice a draft like that.    HAHAHAHA     Good press move, though.    Gross.   
 
    Everyone and their mom is getting divorced.    There should be a ban on celebrity marriages, it creates this image about marriage that I hate.    My parents have been happily married for 25 YEARS now... THAT is what marriage is.    Not a publicity stunt, not a sham!   
 
    Weather...  it is currently 70 and sunny in Anaheim.    If you're not here, well... you're screwed cuz I don't know where you ARE, and I am not catering to anyone.  hahahaha  jk
 
    Drama.    Quit it.    Queens.    haha    Yeah I mean you, jerks!    Always with the drama... why don't we try growing up for a minute, honestly.    For shame!   
 
    Alright, I guess I should actually work some today.  For anyone who's interested, here is an open invitation to have drinks with myself and my Sir on Friday at Tropics Lounge in Fullerton.  $3.00 beers all night, $8.00 pitchers and relatively inexpensive, and strong drinks, too!  My phone is now working too, so you can call me if you dare.  :)

Cell Blockage
 This is my sham of a cell blockage aka "When Co-Workers Collide"
 
    Do you remember those exercises when you were a child where you were given a paper with a scene on it and were then asked "what/who does NOT belong"?    I am playing that game at work today.   
 
    As I sat down I noticed that my trash can was once again BEHIND me, next to my large cabinet drawers.  I had left a note ON the trash can saying to not move it.  It didn't work.  I changed it to spanish.  Still not working.  WTF do I have to do?  GLUE IT TO MY CARPET!?  lol  It's really a miniscule issue, however, it's annoying, and when EVERY day you have to move it for THREE weeks, it gets on your nerves more and more.  Today I am going to try a LARGE sign on TOP of the trash, so they will HAVE to see it to change the bag or empty the trash.  This is WAR!  LOL  jk
 
    Now, upon moving the trash can back to it's preferred spot, I overheard the girl behind me... you know who, talking to someone on the phone.  Last I checked "yeppers" was not only not work-related gab, but OUTDATED by oh about... hmmm... let's see... TEN years.  Maybe more.  Only people who ever said it were the lower class, and the only people who say it NOW are people who may still fall into that category but mostly gangsters, cholos, etc. 
 
    Alright, moving on... a certain somebody's croupy, phlegmy, disgusting cough has returned, and is in FULL effect this morning.  I have a slight scared feeling as I don't want any of that goop projected my way by accident.  SOMEONE SAVE ME!!!  Gross.  L2GTMEDS, right?  hahaha
 
    I finally got my eye doc appmt.  I go Friday at 515p  Then when I'm done, off to Volk's then we'll be going to the bowling alley and then possibly to Fullerton.  Anywho... sounds like it'll be a good night.  I'm really over-excited about getting glasses, mostly cuz I know I NEED them, and because I have to drive home from Joshua Tree with my Oma on the 26th.  I have to remember to make that perfectly clear to the doc too so I don't have to worry about getting my glasses any later than that.  :)  I don't see well at night.  I try to only drive places that I'm familiar with in the dark... and I know my way around over there pretty well now, but I still SHOULD have glasses.  :)  I COULD wear my contacts but I don't want to because I hate them... hehe.  I'm just being a picky stubborn girl... love it, or leave.  hehe jk
 
    Ok I think I'm SO content with today's weather... that I shouldn't be at work cuz it's gonna ruin my  whole day.  But here I am.  Let's ditch! lol jk Alright, that's all for now... later bunnies!

Cell Blockage: Volume 49
I'm REALLY postponing this 50th Anniversary...
 
Popozao, Kevin!  I'm K-Fed up with you!  I want a K-vorce!  Blam!! Fed-Ex'ed... just like that!
 
    I assume most of you have heard about this entertainment drama, and how he would be getting 10mil from her but he's meeting with his law(yers) to try for 30 mil. Are you serious?!  Stupid K-rack addict!  ahahaha
 
    Reportedly they were in a "tiff" on Halloween along with how he stood her up for dinner and she, in revenge, stood him up for presenting some award or something... now he wants custody of the kids, and their 10mil dollar house in Malibu.  Brit might be getting smart again... can't say how long it'll last but she needs to find a man who's not a moocher, and keep her house in the 'bu, too! :)
 
    Let Fed-ex wallow in the  dimes that Popozao will bring in... hahaha.
 
    Unfortunately, this concludes today's issue of Cell Blockage... I had to ease my way back into the newsletter groove, I have lots of work today, and tons of preparation for the almighty 50th anniversary! hehehe jk :)

Short & Sweet
 
    Hello and welcome to issue # 48 of Cell Blockage.  As of late, Cell Blockage has been on a temporary hiatus due to writer's block and willingnessless ( I just wanted to do that... it was on purpose, so you don't have to try and correct me or anything, hehe) to put out Cell Blockage. 
 
    Anyway, how was everyone's Halloween?  Mine was fine, it was fun but not too much fun... but still fun.  Volk and I had a friend's wedding to attend, which was cool.  :)  I had the day off and I also had November 1st off.  On the first, we went to TJ... had some drinks and food and walked around the shops and junk.  It was fun but we should have gotten there earlier to shop at the cart vendors around the corner from Revolucion.  Oh well...
 
    I think I just ate thee most gross sandwich since that one from the machine that had turkey gone bad in it... which, by the way I haven't gone over to get my money back for, yet.  Boo to me!  Anyway, I should learn my lesson...  but I won't.  I forgot my breffies so I had to get something.  Well anyhow, what is everyone doing this weekend?  Tonight, I'm going home to clean cuz my kid, yes, once again, had created hell on earth in my livingroom.  It's really not that it's that much stuff it's just that it's a PAIN to clean up a mess I didn't make.  And getting her to do it takes candy and convincing, HAHAHAHA.  I have this lil game we play, I get like m&m minis or candy corns or something equally small that she can have (seemingly) alot of, then every thing she picks up she gets one, and we make it fun.  You know, like Mary Poppins but more like Scary Poppins... Practically Perfect Enough.  HAHA jk  Anyway, it's a pain in my butt.  I actually have to go buy M&M Minis on my break today so I don't forget to do it later...  so who's walkin with me to the gas station?  :) Hmmmm?
 
    I'm kinda over this right now... have a good weekend bunnies!

Cell Blockage: Volume 47
... I think.
 
    Well, it's been a few days since the last Cell Blockage.    I was busy, I had a day off, etc etc.    Anyway, today it's back!
 
    I have to admit, my weekend was as full as it's been in a long time, but still somewhat uneventful.    I can't say I hated it though... I actually liked it for the most part.    We went to Oktoberfest briefly on Friday, then back to Volk's house to get "f'ed up" as I put it beforehand.    We drank, we fought, we acted like 12 year olds, for the most part... it was really fun!  :)  I got some aggression out and so did Volk (for once, hahaha).    That was awesome!    D found something in the couch cushions that has been lost for a long time, which was funny...  and Nicki left her glasses at Volk's.    Later, as we were going to bed, I noticed Volk was wearing them.    DRUNK!    That's all I have to say about that.    Oh, one more thing... I put those glasses on and now I have NO idea how Nicki drove withOUT them, hahahahaha!
 
    So, on Saturday we, actually just I, got up at 915a and was like "oh yeah... Disneyland today!".    Then I looked over at Volk, and he was sleeping like the dead, so I tried to go back to sleep, which worked for about half an hour. By then, he was ready to get up, we layed around for another hour I think though, before getting up to get ready.    Once, ready we went... it was fun, but BUSY!    REALLY BUSY!    I made Volk go on Tower of Terror with me, cuz it's pretty much the best ride there, even though he hates it, he was a good sport, and I appreciate that.  :)  We didn't end up getting home from Disneyland until around 930p, so we got dressed and headed to the party (next door,  hehe)    Sadly it looked like it was good, but there were only about 6 people left when we got there, we stayed a bit, then went home.    We contemplated going elsewhere cuz we had an alternate plan in Fullerton, but decided against it afterall.    I didn't go all out on my costume due to time but I still looked cute and I have some pics I will put up in the near future.     Sunday, we went to Oktoberfest again, it was the last day, it was nice out, so why not, right?  Yeah, so it was a good day, stayed like 4 hours, had chicken for lunch, let Maya play on the bouncies, met up with a couple friends, it was chill.
 
    Tomorrow is Halloween... and I plan on going ALL OUT with my costume, which isn't much, honestly but it looked so cute Saturday, without the dead looking makeup, without long fake eyelashes, without the whip, etc.    It makes me just want to take those extra steps even though I'll probly be just handing out candy and scaring some children, but that's almost more exciting than anything else, honestly.    hahaha    :)
 
    I bought some papaya mango air freshener stuff for my house, and omg when I woke up this morning it was quite pleasant, I must admit.    I really like this smell for some reason.    This particular brand, actually.    It's Airwick.  I have the wall mount (bathroom style) automatic air freshener already, so I bought a refill for that, and then I got two oil plug-in ones and a spray one, so every room has one, HAHAHA I am all about having one smell in the whole place, not like one vanilla room, one lavender room, etc.  No mixing the smells, yo.  LOL    Anyway, I also got these cool kitty litter liners, it's like one liner at the bottom, then 10 slotted liners on top, and each time it's time to clean it out, you just lift up the top one and the clean litter falls through, and so on.  I'm trying to think of ways to make clean up SH!+, easier, honestly.  hehe Volk's grandma has a litter box that he bough for her that her cat doesn't use, so I will be getting that but in the meantime, this will make things much easier.
 
    Ok, I need your opinion... so I mentioned those oil plug-in air fresheners earlier.    Do you think it's ok to put one of those in my cube?    I mean I have to smell all this nasty fish stew and crap all the time (Dina knows what I'm talkin about... BOILED SOCKS! HAHAHAHA), so personally, I don't see why I couldn't use an air freshener... right?    What do you think?    These things are adjustable by the way, you can set it to produce alot or very little scent... so I can just set it accordingly so it's not taking over the whole office (which it SHOULD, lol jk).
 
    Last night I cut my hand, and since I can't wear bandaids, I keep hitting it on stuff, it's on the top of my rt hand just aboe my pointer finger knuckle, SUCKS... oush! 
 
    One more thing, I have just about THEE healthiest lunch today, so who's gonna sit with my while I eat it.    I have two slices of a CA Roll, a sandwich size ziploc of organic spring mix salad, a low fat vanilla yogurt, and a cup of miso (hungry. <-- had to be there, hahahaha). Mmmm yummy runch! 
 
    Is it break time yet?
 
    Ok bye Bunnies!

Cell Blockage: Volume 44
You're My Mirror, Everything I do I see in you
 
Fact:
 
    In case you haven't noticed, the last couple days' second lines have been song lyrics.  This is Tina dico's "mirror", and I believe the other day was Rilo Kiley's "Picture of Success"  Anyway, just an interesting (or totally unnecessary) tidbit.
 
Lie:
 
    I had a wonderful morning, full of raindows and butterflies with sunshine on top!
 
Why:
 
        Because a tanker trunk full of GASoline turned on his blinker as I was just behind his front tires and proceeded to move into my lane.  I was in the rightmost lane and swerved to the bitch lane to avoid the jerk.  I can honestly say it was probably an honest mistake, as my car is tiny, but still... I would have died.  Me in my lil sardine can of a car, with Maya, between a tanker and an overpass... seriously.  Death.
 
And now:
 
    Totally fine.  Still fragile based on the start of the day but I'm good.  Got here late bye accident and was pissed off but realized "I have no obligations but to shit here and look cute, which is not hard for me cuz I have good genes" LOL just kidding folks, omg... But seriously.  I have only a lil bit of work that I plan on stretching through the whole day. AHHHH thanks! Karma has been good to me today. :)
 
In the furture:
 
    Oh god you guys... only 11 days (not including the rest of today) until halloween, and only 7 days until friday, the 27th which marks the start of halloween weekend!!! WEUUUUUTEMOUS! lol jk
    Does anyone not have a costume?  Does anyone need help?  Ideas? Etc?
    I still haven't put my costume together yet.  I will experiment with different things tonight.  I can think about the makeup more last-minute but the costume itself needs to be thoroughly thought out beforehand or it will just not be cute.  In case anyone doesn't know what I'm gonna do yet, I think (I said think, yes) I'm gonna be a dead harajuku girl.  We'll see how this turns out, I might change my mind midway, hehe.
 
    I am obsessed with this fricken holiday.  I am determined to live it out as long as I can, honestly.  If I end up buying a x-mas tree (which will be FAKe, by the way, cuz I don't do real trees as long as I have to transport it, set it up, take it down, etc etc all by myself just for me to look at it and dread the tear-down, daily... no way.  Anyway, if I get a fake tree, it will be nightmare before xmas or have some sort of dark twist I'm sure... i don't think Maya should have to go without a tree but I don't think I should have to have some ugly piece of jesus ornaments hanging on it either. haha I'm not the devil, nor do I believe in him really, I just feel the same about god.  I embrace the holiday based on traditions but not religion I guess... so I'd like to reflect that lack of religious value in my tree.  Cuz you know, my tree says it all and everything, hahahahaha jk
 
    This concludes today's edition of cell blockage

WELKOM to CELL BLOCKAGE: VOLUME 40

RUBIES are the traditional gift of the 40th Anniversary... bright, red, and beautiful.  Nothing like Cell Blockage has been as of late.  I do not apologize.  And, while it's been a fast 40 issues, it suprisingly doesn't seem so. 

During this time, many fits have passed, many racial slurs and jokes have been flung around, many laughs have been had, many a bad day, a good day, a cold day, lately, have been had.  And each of these days have one thing in common...  Cell Blockage.  Admit not that you cannot live without it, that you love it, that you hate it, that you wish you had thought of it yourself.  Admit only that you look for it.  In your outlook daily, you see that newsletter and you read it, and you decide either a) today's Cell Blockage sucked, or b) that made my day... either opinion having one common factor... you looked, you saw, and you looked again.  Must not be too bad...

Now, as promised, I will [briefly] go over how to use flesh latex for creating open wounds.  Here goes...

First you will go to any Halloween store, buy about 2 small bottles or at least 6oz of FLESH LATEX.  You can use this anywhere on your skin, arms, face, etc The only warning I give is that hair and Flesh Latex make friends.  Be careful when removing, and if at all possible, remove hair where latex will be.  This isn't mandatory, but helpful.  Alright, so wash the skin where you will apply latex, so it will not slide off your greazy self.  Now, let's say you want to create a bullet wound on your forehead... you will apply about a dime sized, 1/8" thick dot of flesh latex with a q-tip to your forehead.  Arrange it so it is an evenly distributed spot.  Let dry.  You can blowdry it dry but it will probably only take like 30 seconds.  This is the best part!  Now you're going to pinch the center of the "wound" and twist slightly, then PULL UP.  This will break the spot open.  Now gently roll the open edges to the outside, creating a crater-like hole. 

GRATS TO JOOS!  You have just created your first bullet wound, crater, open wound, whatever you want it to be.  Alright, so you want it to be a bullet wound?  Add black grease paint under the open edges of the crater, purple to the center of the hole, and blood around the eges and a little on the outside.  You can change this to an oozing sore by altering the colors to purple, green and black and maybe adding a tiny bit of blood.  Experiment.  This is fun stuff!  

Ok... now onto the more real of the gruesome.  So, imagine this:

Your typical Knott's Scary Farm-type just isn't scary enough... you laugh at the maze, you laugh at other people being scared of the maze, you come out wondering why you even paid however much you paid to get into this place just to think "wow, that wasn't scary".  Did you ever stop to think that maybe you pay for it because you KNOW you won't REALLY be scared?  Would you ACTUALLY pay to walk through a REAL psycho killer's house?  What do you want... to be chased down, hunted and killed for REAL?  No.  That's why all the Halloween mazes suck.  Cuz we know they're not real.  And would you have it any other way?  No.  Unless you're a sick f$%@.  : )   

This leads me to Monday's issue of Cell Blockage... I will be going to Universal's Halloween Horror Nights this Friday (the 13th) and Monday I will review it in comparison to Knott's Scary Farm's event.  We'll see who tried harder!  Keep your eyes peeled...

On a HAPPY NOTE... Gloria, Terri, AND Barb are going to be in some sort of training meeting from 9 (NOW) until 4pm.  F YES! PARRRRTAY! LOL jk  As you all know, this office is like a class of Kindergarteners, we all KNOW how to act but we don't WANT to try... so as soon as the teacher turns to write something on the chalkboard, all HELL breaks loose! LOL jk

Cell Blockage: Volume 39 

Make it a bloody MESS!

In today's issue of Cell Blockage, we'll discuss the techniques, the how-to's, and some tricks to making your scary self look even scarier!

Here's a recipe for BLOOD... it's very easy.

Easy Blood Recipe

      1 pint of clear corn syrup
      1/4 cup of water
      1/4 cup sifted flour or corn starch
      100 drops red food coloring
      8 drops blue food coloring

    First remove about a 1/4 cup of the corn syrup and replace with an equal amount of water. Add the food coloring and mix by gently shaking. Now add the well sifted flour or corn starch and mix again. If flour is used you may get some small lumps in your "blood". We'll call them "clots". Let the bottle sit for a couple of minutes and they will float to the top where you can remove them.

    You can experiment with the amount of materials to get the best blood-like consistency. This formula may temporarily stain skin and may permanently stain clothes because of the food coloring used. Because of the natural sugar content of the corn syrup, this blood does not have a very long shelf live. You can extend the life somewhat by storing the blood in the refrigerator until needed. It sure tastes good!

    For your face, no matter what color you choose, if you use grease paint PLEASE remember to apply a coat of translucent powder to the top, especially if you plan on being somewhere where it's hot, this stuff will DRIP off... seriously! 

    So let's say you want to be a ZOMBIE...  you will need a grey, a green, a red, a purple a brown, and a black paint.  You can buy stacks, like so:

    This is the injury stack, it's good for eveyrthing, really... it comes with a grimy mustard yellow, a blood red, a purple, and a black.  You can probably add green and grey and be a zombie with just these colors alone.

    So here's what you would do.  First, wash your face, you greasy bastard, then pat dry, apply nothing, no moisturizer, toner, zit cream, wrinkle cream, whatever the hell it is you use on that uggmugg of yours.  Leave it bare.

    The first color you will apply will be the grey.  You will use a STIPPLE sponge, and LIGHTLY apply this allover your face down to your neck or lower if you will have your girls out for the night... you want to look uniform.  Hereis a stipple sponge for those of you who are ALREADY confused...

    Only use one side per color of you will mix and it will all be RUINED!  It's hard work your first try so this would be BAD. : )

    Next you will apply green, slightly less coverage than the grey, but concentrate on the hollows of your face, and make it darker there.  Some examples of these spots are your cheekbones, temples, the divot under your nose that connects to the "V" in your top lip, the hollow between your bottom lip and chin, just uner your chin and along the bottom of your jawline, and any other deeper spots you may have, for example, if you have deep set eyes, etc.

    Ok... so now let's work on details.  This is harder.  So, you're going to try to enhance your wrinkles.  Even if you don't have any, you'll find some, or figure out how to fake it.  So you want to scrunch your face up like a bunny wabbit... then HOLD IT there.  Next, take a powder puff or cotton ball and LIGHTLY fluff translucent powder over the wrinkly parts.  Now relax your face.  You will see that where the wrinkles were, there is no powder.... you are going to use a thin eyeliner brush or grey eye pencil to draw in the "creases" this will enhance the depth of the wrinkles making you look more "dead". Be sure not to make the lines too sharp, it actually might be better to blend out a lil tiny bit, too.

     

     

     

     

    Now that that step is done, we're gonna add some yellow, dab it with your ring finger under your eyes, close to the lashes, and then stipple a bit VERY lightly above your cheek hollows, on your cheekbones close to your eyes.  You may do this anywhere else you feel needs a more sallow look. Be creative.

    This is the fun part... you're gonna get your purple and dot a little on here and there where you want there to be wounds. Dear Yahoo!:
How did Halloween get started?
Dwight
Baltimore, Maryland
Dear Dwight:
Halloween has something for everyone. Children scarf candy. Teens smash pumpkins. And dogs go bonkers whenever the doorbell rings. But how did the wild and crazy celebration get its start? We checked in with the History Channel to find out.

The holiday's origins date back to "the ancient Celtic festival of Samhain." Roughly 2,000 years ago, a people known as the Celts lived in the area now divided among three modern-day countries: the United Kingdom, Northern France, and Ireland. The Celts began their new year on November 1, meaning October 31 was their New Year's Eve. According the History Channel, "the boundary between the worlds of the living and the dead became blurred" that night.

Bonfires and animal sacrifices were common, as were costumes "typically consisting of animal heads and skins." Eventually, the Romans conquered the Celts, and Samhain was combined with other holidays. Later, as Christianity became more powerful, Pope Boniface IV put a new tilt on the event. He designated November 1 "All Saints' Day" -- a day when followers could honor saints and martyrs. This celebration was also called "All-Hallows," and the night before (October 31) was known as "All-Hallows' Eve." Later, it became known as Halloween.

These days, Halloween is mostly known as a day when kids throw dental hygiene out the window and go hog-wild with candy. The origin of trick-or-treating is somewhat disputed, but we invite you to check out this essay by Isaac Bonewits. All the possibilities are covered with a minimum amount of trickery.

F/X MAKEUP SAFETY AND INSTRUCTIONS

The instructions here are to help you avoid allot of mistakes and trips to the emergency room. And I'm not and will not be held responsible for anything you may do to yourself. I'm posting plenty of warnings and cautions here for you to see, read and print out. Now that that's out of the way let's get to the good stuff...

Ok... You can use these tips for Stage, Haunted Attractions, and Halloween . And allot of the supplies can be purchased in any Costume Shop, Magic store,  Party store or online at Halloween supplier websites.

Before I get into the do's let me cover allot of the Makeup don'ts because allot of the chemicals can wreck you pretty good.

1. Do not use Crazy Glue or 3M adhesive or anything in the craft glue family on your face or any other body part. "Don't laugh I've seen it done and it's not pretty."

2. Do not use straight plaster to cast any body parts especially your face! You can get second degree burns from it because the plaster gets extremely hot.

3. Use a fan to blow fumes away from your face and whoever you are applying the Appliance or latex on. The fumes from spirit gum and the ammonia in latex can eat layers off of your eyeballs.

4. Do not use red makeup anywhere near your eyes. Use black for close areas and then use the red around it. There is yellow tint that is extremely irritating to your eyes.

5. When using Silver or Gold makeup apply some on a small area on yourself (If it's for you) or whoever it's being used on and give it at least fifteen minutes. Because allot of people are very allergic to those two colors.

6. STAGE BLOOD IS NOT TO BE USED IN YOUR MOUTH! IT MAY SAY NONTOXIC BUT IT WILL MAKE YOU SICK AS A DOG!

7. Do not use Poster paint or shoe polish as makeup.

8. Please, please, please use epoxies and resins outside or in a well I mean really well ventilated area I have a attic fan mounted in the wall of work area. These chemicals can and will turn your brain, liver and kidneys into jelly and make your lungs SOLID.

9. Do not use spray paints, lacquers, paint thinners, or any kind of flammable liquid that gives off fumes around gas hot water heaters (Some of you have them in garage or basement workshops) they have a lower intake vent (to feed air to the pilot flame) because it can and will ignite the fumes.

10. I can't stress enough how important it is to use a respirator. There are allot of chemical solvents and casting material that if inhaled or absorbed can blind you and/or sit in your lungs liver and kidneys forever which will cause later health problems.

11. When welding armatures or sets (For haunts, dark rides etc.) use a welding mask. And if your not doing the work still wear one or just don't look at the weld being done because cornea burns suck. And closing your eyes does not do the trick either the U V light is beyond strong and can go through your eye lids. 

12. When building electric props please, please, please make sure that you have it unplugged before servicing it. And always start with low pressure when doing air cannons or pistons. "I know sounds like common sense stuff, but there is no rewind button if you (F) up seriously and get injured."       

Here's the do's

1. When using red or green or yellow makeup apply a light coat of cold cream on your face. It makes the removal allot easier.

2. Use Seabreeze or Clean and Clear after using cold cream or any oil based makeup remover to clean it out of your pores.

3. Read any and all instructions that come with makeup kits.

4. Use latex, spirit gum or medical adhesive to glue appliances on.     

5. Use latex appliance prep before using greasepaint on them. Use a very light coat of it and it will keep the appliance from looking dull next to you skin. Or use latex mask paint.

6. KY jelly and red food coloring makes excellent stay put blood that looks runny and shiny. Red food coloring can also be mixed with Vaseline for thicker inner wound stay put blood. For older looking blood add small amounts of blue food coloring.

7. If your used to using cotton and latex makeup and want to build up areas fiber fill works better than cotton because it doesn't get as stringy as cotton can with latex. 

8. If you need to have blood pouring out of your mouth and aren't diabetic Kayro Syrup can me mixed with red and or a little blue food coloring for mouth use. Water can be added to make it as flowing as you like. Coffee grounds mixed in give it a gross texture too.

9. When casting teeth have the person lean slightly forward.

10. Always, always, always use any paints and or chemicals in a well ventilated area.

11. A dust mask is not the same thing as a respirator!  A dust mask should only be used for sanding primer, bondo, fiberglass, foam and with plaster powder. Paints and any solvents should only be used with a respirator and always keep a clean filter in it.

12. Use latex gloves when using solvents and certain paints. They can be absorbed through your skin.

Dick Smith's Special Effects Makeup "Creating life cast and appliances."

Tom Savini's Grand Illusions I and II "Creating life cast appliances and props."

Corson's Stage makeup "Great resource for highlights and shadows and applying false beards and hair."

Makeup Monsters "The book that got me started."

California's Supreme Court affirmed Thompson's sentence in 1990, but he continued to pursue federal appeals.

All Things Thirty
 
  Thirty is the atomic number of Zinc, the number of days in the months April, June, September, and November, and in rare cases, February.
  Thirty is the total number of major and minor keys in Western tonal music, including enharmonic equivalents.
  A polygon with thirty sides is called a tricontagon. Both an icosahedron and a dodecahedron have 30 edges.
 
 

Get Educated 

 

  A pearl is a hard, rounded object produced by certain animals, primarily mollusks such as o oysters. Pearls can be used in jewelry and also crushed in cosmetics or paint. Pearl is valued as a gemstone and is cultivated or harvested for jewellery. The pearl is also the birthstone of June.

  Pearls are formed inside the shell of certain bivalve mollusks. As a response to an irritating parasite inside its shell, the mollusk will deposit layers of calcium carbonate (CaCO3) in the form of the minerals aragonite or calcite (both crystalline forms of calcium carbonate) held together by an organic horn-like compound called conchiolin. This combination of calcium carbonate and conchiolin is called nacre, or as most know it, mother-of-pearl. The idea that a grain of sand acts as a "seed" for the pearl is a myth.

Cell Blockage: Volume 15 - Tired Edition
 
  My eventful Wednesday has made me a tired lil bunny...
 
  To begin the day's fun, I woke up at 830a and procrastinated on the internet until 9a when I finally decided to get ready.  So I get ready and head over to Anaheim to my court hearing, which began at 1030a.  I sat in the lobby aread from 1030a-1245p before I went in for my pre-hearing interview.  In the interview, they go over the case info and make sure everything is correct and show proof of income, etc etc.  So I did that and was back in the waiting area by 100p (if that)  where I proceeded to wait for them to talk to Art (Maya's dad).  So we both agree on the amt of hrs we have care of Maya, and the amt of money we make, etc etc. and decide that rather than going into court, we would like to just sign a stipulation stating that we agree and what we agree upon and the girl goes to talk to the lawyer to draw up some paperwork and there's a complication with some taxable income he rec'vs from the military.  Long story short, he agrees to leave that taxable income on the stipulation as payment for the medical care that I will get for Maya via Fremont.  All in all it was a good outcome.  He doesn't suffer (at all, actually) and neither do I.  I went from $230.00/month to $432.00/month.  That is gonna help out ALOT, let me tell you. 
 
  After that, I went to Volk's to wash my car.  He was working on his latest project in his room and I layed down on the bed to make a couple calls, finished that and fell asleep.  Then about an hour later I would say, Volk is like "Val... Ryan is here" and I didn't know why Ryan was there but he just stopped by after work I guess.  We all hung out til about 630p when I had to leave to meet Tori and Deanne at Tori's house and then we went out to Sushi.  That alone was an ordeal, just finding this Sushi place where we were going, cuz we were given bunk directions. haha  Anyway, we met up at 7 and we FINALLY got there at around 830ish.  We sat down, took like 20 mins to finally choose everything and order... then we ate, it was delish, and 100.00 later, the four of us left sushi.  Deanne, Tori, and I went back to Tori's where we drank a lil more except D, who drank ALOT more, hahaha  I got home at about 130a and stayed up til 2a
 
  I woke up at 715a and literally stumbled, tired to the bathroom and showered and got ready, and I actually got here 5 mins early. CAN YOU IMAGINE!? lol jk
 
  All in all, it was a good night... and now I know I don't hate sushi, like I did when I first had it when I was 12. : ) Now if only Friday would come faster.  And F Erika for not being here YET AGAIN!  Some people should NOT pro-create.  Actually I don't even know why they would call that PRO-creating... there are NO PROS about it.
